21 position of civil penalties under this section; and
22 (f) Allow an animal rescue entity to have an opportunity for judicial review of the impo-
23 sition of civil penalties.
24 (7) Consistent with the rulemaking procedures set forth in ORS chapter 183, in developing
25 rules to implement this section, the department shall solicit and review input from:
26 (a) Animal rescue entities located in rural areas of this state;
27 (b) Animal rescue entities located in urban areas of this state;
28 (c) Individuals or organizations involved in providing transportation to or from animal
29 rescue entities in this state; and
30 (d) Individuals or organizations involved in providing free or low-cost services relating
31 to the care of animals in this state.
32 SECTION 2. ORS 609.420 is amended to read:
33 609.420. (1) Whenever an authorized representative of [an enforcing agency] the State Depart-
34 ment of Agriculture is advised or has reason to believe that an animal rescue entity that is re-
35 quired to obtain a license under ORS 609.415 is operating without a license, the authorized
36 representative may visit and conduct an on-site investigation of the premises of the animal rescue
37 entity. The purpose of an investigation under this section is to determine whether the animal rescue
38 entity is subject to the requirements of ORS 609.415.
39 (2) At any reasonable time, an authorized representative of [an enforcing agency] the depart-
40 ment, a law enforcement agency or the United States Department of Agriculture may conduct an
41 on-site investigation of the premises of any licensed animal rescue entity to determine whether the
42 entity is in compliance with ORS 609.415 or a rule adopted thereunder.
43 (3) An authorized representative of the [enforcing agency] State Department of Agriculture
44 or a law enforcement agency shall conduct an on-site investigation of the premises of any licensed
45 animal rescue entity if the department or agency receives a complaint about the animal rescue
